<note id="fs-id1167067031400" class="learning-objectives">
<label/>
<title>Section Learning Objectives</title>
<para id="fs-id1167066972560">By the end of the section, you will be able to do the following:</para>
<list id="fs-id1167063891721"><item>Define, describe, and differentiate the four fundamental forces</item>
<item>Describe the carrier particles and explain how their exchange transmits force</item>
<item>Explain how particle accelerators work to gather evidence about particle physics</item>
</list></note>

<note id="fs-id1167066959976" class="os-teacher">
<title>Teacher Support</title>
<para id="fs-id1167063680522">The learning objectives in this section will help your students master the following standards:</para>
<list id="fs-id1167066104240"><item>(5) Science concepts. The student knows the nature of forces in the physical world. The student is expected to:
<list id="fs-id1167067158485"><item>(H) describe evidence for and effects of the strong and weak nuclear forces in nature.</item>
</list></item></list></note>
