<para id="fs-id1164565506969">If the strong attractive force is the greatest of the four fundamental forces, are all masses fated to combine together at some point in the future? Explain.</para>
<list id="fs-id1164567841496" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>No, the strong attractive force acts only at incredibly small distances. As a result, only masses close enough to be within its range will combine.</item>
<item>No, the strong attractive force acts only at large distances. As a result, only masses far enough apart will combine.</item>
<item>Yes, the strong attractive force acts at any distance. As a result, all masses are fated to combine together at some point in the future.</item>
<item>Yes, the strong attractive force acts at large distances. As a result, all masses are fated tocombine together at some point in the future.</item>
</list>
</problem>
